    "MissionType": {
        "UUID": "5e727c38-d43e-445f-95b2-a971428dd06d",
        "Name": "Resource Drive - ArcCorp"
    },
    "MissionGiver": "ArcCorp",
    "Title": "RESOURCE DRIVE: BRING US MATERIALS",
    "Description": "ArcCorp is still competing for top spot in the resource race, so we need reliable contractors like you to supply us with refined materials. Unsurprisingly, every shop is completely sold out of these, but luckily we\u2019ve got a list of suggestions where to mine them along with what you'll earn:\n\n- <EM4>Copper</EM4> (surface of Aberdeen) - <EM4>803 aUEC</EM4> per SCU\n- <EM4>Tungsten</EM4> (surface of Lyria) - <EM4>1080 aUEC</EM4> per SCU\n- <EM4>Corundum</EM4> (surface of ArcCorp) - <EM4>810 aUEC</EM4> per SCU\n\nMake sure you get them refined before you hand them over, otherwise you\u2019ll just make more work for us. <EM4>ARC-L1 Wide Forest Station</EM4> is a good option, but we don\u2019t mind where you go so long as it gets done. Then, all you have to do is take the refined materials to a freight elevator at: <EM4>~mission(Destination|Address|ListAll)</EM4>. Oh, and make sure to submit the contract when you\u2019re happy with the total amount you delivered.\n\nIf you haven't mined in a while, I suggest taking a look at URW's <EM4>\u201cThe Fundamentals of Mining\u201d</EM4> in your mobiGlas Journal. That should give you a few pointers.\n\nAnd just so you know, each company has to declare publicly how much they\u2019ve given to the cause. You can track this information, including who is leading in the initiative, in the <EM4>Second Life Resource Drive</EM4> Journal entry. ArcCorp have very generously agreed to give out additional rewards when contractors meet certain delivery thresholds. How nice is that?\n\nGood luck and talk soon!\n\n\nElla Tieno\nContractor Liaison Officer\nArcCorp",
